profile_positions.description:
Building data pipelines and analytical tools for the Convolo platform (brightnorth.co.uk/platform), a suite of microservice applications with a focus on e-commerce.

• Built a data analytics pipeline for monitoring the performance of an engine processing 100K images on a daily basis (shell, Logstash, ElasticSearch, AWS, Redshift);
• Developed supervised learning engine for classifying product information (production system in Clojure and the JVM, proof of concept in R and Python, training data via a CasperJS/Clojure framework);
• Led a team in the development of an ad-tech product from brainstorm to proof-of-concept.

Lots of exposure to a full stack data-workflow:
• data engineering (set-up of data warehouses, Redshift & other databases, Torch, ElasticSearch instances, NoSQL tools, ...);
• data analysis & exploration (R, Python, Tableau visualisation, other dashboard tools);
• communication & consulting (project-based work in agile setting, building tailored reporting options and presentations where user experience is paramount).

Mostly client-side consultancy work in small teams, which gave me the opportunity to develop a wide array of both technical and non-technical skills in a short amount of time.

• Sky: built a reporting data warehouse (Redshift & Postgres), implemented and productionised a high performance attribution model to quantify impact of branding campaigns (parallelised R on AWS, blog.brightnorth.co.uk/2014/04/11/two-million-regressions-an-hour/). Won DataIQ award (blog.brightnorth.co.uk/2014/06/19/bright-north-and-bskyb-win-at-dataiq-awards/);

• Guardian News&Media: project-lead in the production of a Tableau dashboard aggregating the results of GNM’s online marketing campaigns (Oracle, Tableau, R);

• JP Morgan: developed a recommendation system aggregating 300,000+ low-level user systems to simplify role-management of staff (data engine built in Oracle and ElasticSearch, interfaced with an Angular.js front-end);

• The Share Centre: analysed the performance of their marketing channels for sign-up efficiency, visualised results in a live marketing dashboard (attribution model in R, reporting in Tableau).
